CALCUTTA police in Mpumalanga are searching for a suspect after a 27-year-old man was murdered. Nkosinathi Moropane was shot on the chest while sitting with his girlfriend and grandmother at Marite Jim Brown trust near Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga, on Thursday night. According to police spokesman Brigadier Leonard Hlathi, cops received a report that a man had been shot and killed. Upon arrival at the scene, they found the victim lying face up. He was unconscious, bleeding from the mouth and chest. “Emergency services were summoned for assistance, but the victim was unfortunately certified dead. Through a preliminary investigation, it appeared the victim was shot two times on his chest. A cartridge was found next to his body, and the suspect reportedly ran away,” Hlathi said. “The suspect and motive for the killing are unknown. We appeal to anyone with information to contact Lieutenant Colonel Duduzile Shabangu at 082 469 2569 or Detective Sergeant Sibusiso Sibuyi on 076 128 9157.”